Baltika of Estonia Fourth-Quarter Loss Narrows on Cost Cuts

-- B y   O t t   U m m e l a s
-- 
2011-02-28T15:15:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-28/baltika-of-estonia-fourth-quarter-loss-narrows-on-cost-cuts.html
AS Baltika, the third-largest Baltic
clothing retailer, posted a narrower fourth-quarter loss on
lower operating costs and said it may exit the Polish market.  The net loss narrowed to 20 million krooni ($1.8 million)
from 32.9 million krooni a year earlier, the Tallinn, Estonia-
based company said today in a regulatory  statement . Revenue rose
7 percent to 236 million krooni.  Baltika said it will decide within the next six months on
whether to exit the Polish market.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ott Ummelas in Tallinn at 
 oummelas@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Willy Morris at 
 wmorris@bloomberg.net  